scene.message:
Nanjo: So, where to next? I{nl}
don't mind where, so long as{nl}
we reach the hospital last.{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: Demons or no, business{nl}
can't take a day off, is that{nl}
it? People are tougher than{nl}
you'd think.{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: Music... that's,{nl}
like, piano and singing?{waitkey}{clearbox}Huh? I feel like I've heard{nl}
something just like that{nl}
somewhere.{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: Is it really okay to{nl}
keep the store open?{waitkey}{clearbox}Don't blame me if a demon{nl}
gets you!{waitkey}{ret}

Elly: Come to think of it,{nl}
someone at school said much{nl}
the same thing.{waitkey}{ret}

Yukino: Enough exploring,{nl}
right? Shall we head to Alaya{nl}
Shrine next?{waitkey}{ret}

Shopkeeper: Oh, welcome.{nl}
My, you've got it rough too,{nl}
haven't you.{waitkey}{ret}

Customer: There's just one{nl}
odd shop in this arcade.{waitkey}{clearbox}It's always closed whenever{nl}
you look, and no one's ever{nl}
seen anyone come or go.{waitkey}{clearbox}But sometimes, they say, you{nl}
can hear music...{wait_fr:48}{nl}
Truly, strange things happen.{waitkey}{ret}

Customer: About that odd{nl}
shop in the arcade.{waitkey}{clearbox}I heard a rumor it's set{nl}
to open soon.{waitkey}{clearbox}When that'll be, though,{nl}
I couldn't tell you.{waitkey}{ret}
